   =20
      Volcano bond
   =20
 =20

Back in 2021, the government of El Salvador hit on what  I thought was a  p=
retty good  idea, for 2021:
=09Issue a sovereign bond worth $50.=09Buy $25 worth of Bitcoin.=09Staple t=
hem together and sell=C2=A0the package =E2=80=94=C2=A0$50 of bond and $25 o=
f Bitcoin =E2=80=94=C2=A0for $100.=09On the blockchain! You could do stuff =
like that, if you did it on the blockchain.=09Use some of the money to buy =
the Bitcoins that go into the package, some to buy more=C2=A0Bitcoins to ga=
mble with El Salvador=E2=80=99s public treasury, and the rest to fund infra=
structure projects.=09Also there was a volcano involved? The volcano would =
generate energy to mine Bitcoins? Why not.

Man, crypto in 2021 was just wild. For one thing, people would make stuff u=
p =E2=80=94=C2=A0new cryptocurrencies, new JPEGs =E2=80=94=C2=A0and sell th=
em for millions of dollars. But also, like,=C2=A0math=C2=A0became kind of w=
oozy, and you could take a crypto thing with a market value of $75 and wave=
 your hands around for a bit and sell it=C2=A0for $100. There were perpetua=
l motion machines everywhere.
Or not. El Salvador tried it, but they never actually sold the bonds, and n=
ow it is 2023 and Frank Muci reports:

The proposal to tokenize a sovereign bond on a blockchain is now officially=
 dead. This summer, Forbes contributor and Tether/Bitfinex spokesperson Jav=
ier Bastardo wrote that El Salvador will =E2=80=9Ctweak the investment sche=
me from issuing public debt [the volcano bond] to private equity funding ro=
unds by the Volcano Energy initiative [a joint venture with the government,=
 private firms and crypto companies]=E2=80=9D.=C2=A0
In other words, some joint venture will raise equity to fund wind and solar=
 energy capacity, but there won=E2=80=99t be debt or a bond. There won=E2=
=80=99t be geothermal energy from the volcano as originally advertised eith=
er, oh well. This post is an obituary, a requiem for the volcano bond and t=
he insanity that was crypto just two years ago.=C2=A0

It is a little hard to believe that any of this was real, and of course in =
an important sense it wasn=E2=80=99t.=C2=A0

