<h2 style=3D"font-weight: bold; font-family: &quot;Arial Black&quot;, Arial=
, Helvetica, sans-serif; letter-spacing: -1px; font-size: 20px; border-bott=
om-width: 1px; border-bottom-style: dotted; margin: 0px; padding: 16px 0px =
5px;">Citadel cell phones</h2>
</td>
</tr>
</table>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The US Securities and Exchange Commission has =
a rule that, if you work in the financial industry, you are only allowed to=
 communicate=C2=A0about work with your colleagues and customers using syste=
ms =E2=80=94=C2=A0like your firm email account or=C2=A0Bloomberg messaging =
=E2=80=94 that your firm can archive and review. You are not allowed to use=
 WhatsApp or Signal or iMessage or text messaging from your personal phone.=
 Financial industry employees have to =E2=80=9Cconduct their communications=
 about business matters within only official channels, and they must mainta=
in and preserve those communications,=E2=80=9D as SEC Chair Gary Gensler <a=
 href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32851551.261423/aHR0=
cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9uZXdzL3ByZXNzLXJlbGVhc2UvMjAyMi0xNzQ/607f07ceef4b852=
4a319a23cBc6db2938" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=
=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: so=
lid; background-color: #ccc;">put it last year</a>, when he fined 15=C2=A0b=
anks a total of $1.1 billion for using WhatsApp.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This is a weird rule that the SEC has. For one=
 thing, it is obviously not the rule. Gensler=C2=A0<em>cannot possibly have=
 meant=C2=A0</em>that investment bankers and traders are only allowed to co=
mmunicate about business using corporate email and Bloomberg messages and r=
ecorded phone lines; he is=C2=A0<em>surely=C2=A0</em>aware that sometimes a=
 banker will turn to the colleague sitting next to her and say, aloud, =E2=
=80=9Chey did you finish that pitch deck yet,=E2=80=9D and that she will so=
metimes fly out to meet with a client in a conference room (or on a golf co=
urse) and talk business face to face. Plenty of business communication stil=
l occurs informally, in person, and it can=E2=80=99t=C2=A0be preserved unti=
l you get every employee into augmented reality goggles that record everyth=
ing.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">For another thing, this rule =E2=80=94=C2=A0th=
at you have to do business communications only on official channels =E2=80=
=94=C2=A0is a somewhat new interpretation of the SEC=E2=80=99s=C2=A0actual =
written rules=C2=A0say. When all those banks got in trouble last year, <a h=
ref=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32851551.261423/aHR0cH=
M6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9maWxlcy9saXRpZ2F0aW9uL2FkbWluLzIwMjIvMzQtOTU5MjQucGRm/=
607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB517b1fb5" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"item=
scope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !im=
portant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bot=
tom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">they got in trouble for</a> viol=
ating SEC <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32851551=
.261423/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cubGF3LmNvcm5lbGwuZWR1L2Nmci90ZXh0LzE3LzI0MC4xN2EtNA/=
607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBb6e6c351" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"item=
scope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !im=
portant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bot=
tom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">Rule 17-4(b)(4)</a>, which requi=
res broker-dealers to =E2=80=9Cpreserve for a period of not less than three=
 years =E2=80=A6=C2=A0originals of all communications received and copies o=
f all communications sent (and any approvals thereof) by the member, broker=
 or dealer (including inter-office memoranda and communications) relating t=
o its business as such.=E2=80=9D I have <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloomb=
ergbusiness.com/click/32851551.261423/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vc=
GluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjItMDktMjgvdGhlLWRlbGktd2FzLWFsbGVnZWRseS1hLWZyYXVk=
P2NtcGlkPUJCRDA5MjcyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1=
uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMDkyNyZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07c=
eef4b8524a319a23cBee804dc6" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" =
target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important=
; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-sty=
le: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> pointed out before</a> that this rule =
was written in 1948, when =E2=80=9Cinter-office memoranda=E2=80=9D were a t=
hing, and when it made sense to talk about keeping =E2=80=9Coriginals=E2=80=
=9D and =E2=80=9Ccopies=E2=80=9D of communications because they were writte=
n on typewriters with carbon paper.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">This record-keeping requirement was originally=
 meant to apply to fairly=C2=A0<em>formal=C2=A0</em>written communications,=
 because it was written=C2=A0back when written communications were necessar=
ily formal. But now that everyone texts all the time, the requirement has b=
ecome=C2=A0<em>vastly broader:=C2=A0</em>Everything that would have been an=
 informal face-to-face chat in 1948 is a text message now, and so is swept =
up in the SEC=E2=80=99s interpretation of its rule. It doesn=E2=80=99t seem=
 like quite what the rule meant.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But you can see why the SEC loves its current =
rule, Gensler=E2=80=99s rule, the one about all communications being on pre=
served official channels. There are two reasons:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">This rule is really good for regulati=
on and enforcement. If all business communications have to occur on officia=
l channels and be preserved, then the SEC will have an easy time investigat=
ing misbehavior: If it has any suspicions about anything, it can call a fir=
m and say =E2=80=9Cgive me all the=C2=A0messages that Employee X sent about=
 Topic Y last year,=E2=80=9D and the firm will run a search and hand over t=
he messages. It can call=C2=A0<em>every=C2=A0</em>firm and ask them that. T=
he firms themselves will do it voluntarily: Their compliance people will co=
nstantly run searches on their internal messages, looking for keywords like=
 =E2=80=9Cfraud=E2=80=9D or whatever, and then hand anything bad over to th=
e SEC. There are not a lot of areas where every crime is meticulously docum=
ented in written electronic messages that are preserved and handed over to =
regulators. Obviously the coverage is not perfect, and there will still be =
golf courses and in-person meetings, but I suppose in the long run technolo=
gy (goggles, etc.)=C2=A0might stamp those out too and the SEC will achieve =
a perfect panopticon.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">This rule is=
=C2=A0<em>new</em>, so it is=C2=A0<em>lucrative</em>. Financial firms and t=
heir employees=C2=A0<em>really did not know=C2=A0</em>about the SEC rule th=
at nobody could use WhatsApp to message their colleagues, because, again, t=
hat=E2=80=99s a somewhat=C2=A0novel interpretation of the actual rules. And=
 so when the SEC decided, in <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness=
.com/click/32851551.261423/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9uZXdzL3ByZXNzLXJlbGVh=
c2UvMjAyMS0yNjI/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB802cf572" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" i=
temscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-deco=
ration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #00=
0000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">about=C2=A02021<=
/a> =E2=80=94=C2=A0when everyone was working from home due to Covid and sen=
ding lots of text messages =E2=80=94 that texting about work was illegal, e=
very single bank was doing illegal things. And so the SEC could just kind o=
f go down the line and extract a $125 million fine from each of them. It di=
dn=E2=80=99t have to prove any=C2=A0<em>bad=C2=A0</em>behavior: It got samp=
les of the bankers=E2=80=99=C2=A0text and WhatsApp messages and, as far as =
I can tell, never found a single text message relating to any sort of misco=
nduct. It just had to prove that there were text messages about business an=
d, boom, $125 million. =E2=80=9CIt is not literally the case that the US Se=
curities and Exchange Commission is a for-profit business whose goal is to =
maximize its revenue,=E2=80=9D <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusine=
ss.com/click/32851551.261423/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2=
FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDItMDIvdGhlLXNlYy13YW50cy10by1zZWUtbW9yZS1waG9uZXM_Y21wa=
WQ9QkJEMDkyNzIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3Ns=
ZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMwOTI3JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b85=
24a319a23cB98524a17" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=
=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: so=
lid; background-color: #ccc;"> I once wrote</a>, about this business, but, =
man. This is a profitable business.</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The SEC extracted all of those fines through s=
ettlements with the banks. I suppose the banks could say =E2=80=9Cno, see y=
ou in court,=E2=80=9D but I don=E2=80=99t think any have. The SEC=E2=80=99s=
 interpretation of the rule is aggressive, but it=E2=80=99s logical, and it=
 is pretty risky for the banks to fight the SEC on this.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Anyway this rule is so good that, after fining=
 the banks $125 million each for violating it, the SEC has moved on to othe=
r financial firms. It has long <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusine=
ss.com/click/32851551.261423/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydG=
ljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDItMDIvd2hhdHNhcHAtcHJvYmUtaGl0cy1iaWctaGVkZ2UtZnVuZHMtYXMtc=
2VjLWFza3MtZm9yLXBob25lLXJldmlldz9jbXBpZD1CQkQwOTI3MjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1f=
bWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMzA5MjcmdXRtX2N=
hbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBafe4dfa1" itemprop=3D"Sto=
ryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; =
text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-c=
olor: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> been r=
eported</a> that hedge funds, private equity firms and other investment man=
agers <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32851551.261=
423/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDktMjUvc2V=
jLWNvbGxlY3RzLXByaXZhdGUtbWVzc2FnZXMtaW4td2hhdHNhcHAtcHJvYmUtcmV1dGVycy1zYX=
lzP2NtcGlkPUJCRDA5MjcyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZ=
T1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMDkyNyZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f0=
7ceef4b8524a319a23cBa2613c5d" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope=
" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !importa=
nt; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-s=
tyle: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> are next</a>: There are a lot of the=
m, they have deep pockets, surely they=E2=80=99ve sent some text messages. =
It would be good, for the SEC, to extract money out of them, and it would b=
e good to<em>=C2=A0</em>apply<em>=C2=A0</em>Gensler=E2=80=99s rule to them =
going forward, so that if they do any crimes in the future they will have m=
eticulous records of those crimes to hand over to the SEC.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">There is a bit of a problem with moving on to =
investment managers, which is that Rule 17-4(b)(4) =E2=80=94=C2=A0the rule =
that=C2=A0requires broker-dealers to preserve their communications, and tha=
t the SEC uses as the basis for its =E2=80=9Conly official channels=E2=80=
=9D rule =E2=80=94=C2=A0does not apply to investment managers. Investment m=
anagers=C2=A0<em>do=C2=A0</em>have a communications-preservation rule, <a h=
ref=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32851551.261423/aHR0cH=
M6Ly93d3cubGF3LmNvcm5lbGwuZWR1L2Nmci90ZXh0LzE3LzI3NS4yMDQtMg/607f07ceef4b85=
24a319a23cB7358156a" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=
=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; bord=
er-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: so=
lid; background-color: #ccc;">Rule 204-2(a)(7)</a>, but it is narrower, cov=
ering external communications about specific topics (investment recommendat=
ions and advice, trade orders, etc.), not the manager=E2=80=99s =E2=80=9Cbu=
siness as such.=E2=80=9D In January a bunch of asset-management=C2=A0trade =
associations <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32851=
551.261423/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2lmbWEub3JnL3dwLWNvbnRlbnQvdXBsb2Fkcy8yMDIzLzAy=
L0ludmVzdG1lbnQtQWR2aXNlci1SZWNvcmRrZWVwaW5nLVJlcXVpcmVtZW50cy5wZGY/607f07c=
eef4b8524a319a23cBc4acdda9" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" =
target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important=
; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-sty=
le: solid; background-color: #ccc;">sent a letter to the SEC</a> arguing =
=E2=80=9Cthat the SEC is attempting to exceed its authority under the Advis=
ers Act and<br />engaging in rulemaking by enforcement through its current =
sweep regarding off-channel communications,=E2=80=9D and that Rule 204-2(a)=
(7) does not cover the sort of intra-desk text messaging that the SEC has b=
een going after at the banks.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Still I basically assume that the SEC will jus=
t go down the line extracting flat but lower-than-$125-million fines from a=
ll the hedge funds, private equity firms, etc. But maybe not? Bloomberg=E2=
=80=99s <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32851551.2=
61423/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDktMjcvd=
XMtZ292ZXJubWVudC1zaHV0ZG93bi1zLWVjb25vbWljLXJpc2tzLWdyb3ctdGhlLWxvbmdlci1p=
dC1sYXN0cz9jbXBpZD1CQkQwOTI3MjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaXVtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9=
zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMzA5MjcmdXRtX2NhbXBhaWduPW1vbmV5c3R1Zm=
Y/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB7fcb1bc5" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"it=
emscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !=
important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-b=
ottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> Austin Weinstein reports</a>:=
</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Citadel is preparing to push back against the =
Securities and Exchange Commission=E2=80=99s WhatsApp probe, taking a harde=
r line than the almost two dozen banks that have paid hefty settlements ove=
r the past two years.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Ken Griffin=E2=80=99s hedge fund has told indu=
stry peers that it plans to battle the SEC if the regulator moves against C=
itadel, according to people familiar with the talks. And it=E2=80=99s willi=
ng to take the agency to court, said the people, who asked not to be identi=
fied discussing private conversations.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Miami-based firm would be the first to fig=
ht the SEC over any allegations of untracked communications. As a hedge fun=
d, it would likely argue that it=E2=80=99s not subject to the same rules as=
 Wall Street banks like JPMorgan Chase &amp; Co. and Bank of America Corp.,=
 which agreed to pay more than $2.5 billion to settle US regulators=E2=80=
=99 investigations into their employees using unofficial messaging platform=
s for business.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Sure, good for them.</p>
