<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The schematic math of the Sculptor Capital Man=
agement Inc. situation is:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Sculptor is a publicly traded asset m=
anager with about $30 billion of assets under management, roughly half=C2=
=A0in collateralized loan obligations and the rest in hedge fund and real e=
state strategies.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Those $30 billio=
n of client assets pay Sculptor fees of more than $400=C2=A0million per yea=
r.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Of those fees, more than $300 m=
illion per year goes to Sculptor=E2=80=99s employees, with much of it conce=
ntrated among the senior people=C2=A0managing its funds. Its chief executiv=
e officer and chief investment officer, Jimmy Levin, <a href=3D"https://lin=
k.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32851551.261423/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdv=
di9peD9kb2M9L0FyY2hpdmVzL2VkZ2FyL2RhdGEvMTQwMzI1Ni8wMDAxNDAzMjU2MjMwMDAwNzM=
vc2N1LTIwMjMwNDI4Lmh0bSNpNTdjZTBkNDViYjRiNDZhMDhjMDRkNTYzOTNiYjIzODNfMTI3/6=
07f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB82c71afa" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"items=
cope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !imp=
ortant; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bott=
om-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">made $49 million in 2022</a> and =
$146 million in 2021.<a class=3D"footnote-index" href=3D"#footnote-1" style=
=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: =
1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: none !important; ba=
ckground-color: transparent !important; display: inline-block;">
<span>[1]</span>
</a>
</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">A bit less than $0 per year goes =
to Sculptor=E2=80=99s shareholders: The firm <a href=3D"https://link.mail.b=
loombergbusiness.com/click/32851551.261423/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuc2VjLmdvdi9peD9k=
b2M9L0FyY2hpdmVzL2VkZ2FyL2RhdGEvMTQwMzI1Ni8wMDAxNDAzMjU2MjMwMDAwNTEvc2N1LTI=
wMjIxMjMxLmh0bSNpNDFmODQyNDIyMjY5NDc0NWJhY2M1NzFjYmQxZWZiMjVfMzE/607f07ceef=
4b8524a319a23cB72056cd5" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" tar=
get=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important; b=
order-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style:=
 solid; background-color: #ccc;">reported net losses</a> in each of the las=
t two years.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">Being a Sculptor hedg=
e fund manager is quite lucrative, but=C2=A0being a Sculptor shareholder is=
 not particularly.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">This is not a w=
eird anomaly! Being a hedge fund manager is lucrative, and Sculptor is a he=
dge fund management firm that employs hedge fund managers. Most hedge fund =
management firms are privately held, and roughly all of the money goes to t=
he managers. To compete for talent, Sculptor also pays roughly all of its m=
oney to its managers. The shareholders get squeezed. Jimmy Levin did not in=
vent this or anything. Dan Och, Sculptor=E2=80=99s founder and former CEO/C=
IO, =E2=80=9C<a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32851=
551.261423/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDkt=
MjYvYm9hei13ZWluc3RlaW4tY2hhc2VzLWhlZGdlLWZ1bmQtdGl0YW4tc3RhdHVzLXdpdGgtc2N=
1bHB0b3ItYmlkP2NtcGlkPUJCRDA5MjcyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09ZW1haWwmdX=
RtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMDkyNyZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249bW9uZXlzd=
HVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cB834acedb" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=
=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: =
none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; bo=
rder-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;">took home $3.3 billion</=
a> since 2007 as Sculptor=E2=80=99s stock price tanked by 96%.=E2=80=9D Tha=
t=E2=80=99s just how it works!</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">The=
 result is that Sculptor=E2=80=99s stock price is fairly cheap, since the c=
ash flows to shareholders are a bit less than zero.</li>=09<li style=3D"mar=
gin-bottom: 5px;">But if you buy=C2=A0<em>all=C2=A0</em>of Sculptor, you ca=
n make=C2=A0<em>yourself=C2=A0</em>the CEO, and pay yourself all the fees.<=
/li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">As I <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbus=
iness.com/click/32851551.261423/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9=
uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDgtMjMvY291bGQtc2N1bHB0b3ItYmUtYmV0dGVyLW9yLWNoZWFwZX=
I_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDkyNzIzX01PTkVZU1RVRkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlP=
W5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMwOTI3JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07c=
eef4b8524a319a23cB1e67e506" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" =
target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decoration: none !important=
; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-sty=
le: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> wrote last month</a>:</p>
<blockquote><p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">If you have a public company where=
 most of the cash flows go, not to the shareholders, but to the CEO, then i=
t is cheap to become a shareholder and lucrative to become the CEO. But if =
you buy enough shares you can make yourself the CEO. There is an arbitrage.=
</p></blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">I kind of don=E2=80=99t understand why more he=
dge fund managers are not bidding to buy Sculptor. But a bunch of them are,=
 in a consortium led by Boaz Weinstein, and Bloomberg=E2=80=99s Katherine B=
urton and Hema Parmar <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/cl=
ick/32851551.261423/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVzLzI=
wMjMtMDktMjYvYm9hei13ZWluc3RlaW4tY2hhc2VzLWhlZGdlLWZ1bmQtdGl0YW4tc3RhdHVzLX=
dpdGgtc2N1bHB0b3ItYmlkP2NtcGlkPUJCRDA5MjcyM19NT05FWVNUVUZGJnV0bV9tZWRpdW09Z=
W1haWwmdXRtX3NvdXJjZT1uZXdzbGV0dGVyJnV0bV90ZXJtPTIzMDkyNyZ1dG1fY2FtcGFpZ249=
bW9uZXlzdHVmZg/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cC834acedb" itemprop=3D"StoryLink" it=
emscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-decor=
ation: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: #000=
000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> reported yesterd=
ay</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Boaz Weinstein made his name trading in esoter=
ic corners of the credit markets. But his most audacious bet yet may be try=
ing to catapult his hedge fund firm into the ranks of the industry=E2=80=99=
s largest players.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">To do that, the 50-year-old head of Saba Capit=
al Management is attempting to buy his way to the top. He=E2=80=99s bidding=
 =E2=80=94 with a group of billionaire pals including Bill Ackman, Marc Las=
ry and Jeff Yass =E2=80=94 for Sculptor Capital Management Inc., a beleague=
red publicly traded money manager he aims to subsume into his $4 billion fi=
rm.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Weinstein=E2=80=99s assets under management co=
uld balloon to more than $20 billion if he wins Sculptor, requiring only a =
$700 million investment backed by deep-pocketed friends. While Weinstein=E2=
=80=99s group made the highest bid, it was rejected for a lower one from Ri=
thm Capital Corp. Sculptor, which said Rithm=E2=80=99s offer was more certa=
in, won=E2=80=99t let Weinstein speak directly to investors or stockholders=
. =E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Like the chess master he is, Weinstein saw a w=
ay to exploit weak competition and build his empire. Saba=E2=80=99s main fu=
nd is slightly niche =E2=80=93 short bonds, long volatility =E2=80=94 and w=
hile he=E2=80=99s added some other strategies, growing assets is a slow gam=
e.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">So when Sculptor put itself on the block late =
last year, Weinstein assembled his all-star team and made a bid. In July, S=
culptor picked Rithm =E2=80=94 a firm that started out in mortgage servicin=
g rights =E2=80=94 which agreed to pay $11.15 a share, or $639 million. Scu=
lptor rejected Weinstein=E2=80=99s higher bid, which now stands at $12.76. =
=E2=80=A6</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Under Weinstein=E2=80=99s plan, Sculptor would=
 be run as its own brand within Saba. With the current CIO in a lesser role=
, or even gone, Weinstein could use the extra money =E2=80=93 Levin was pai=
d $145 million in 2021 =E2=80=94 to help retain strategy heads and others a=
mong its 100 investment professionals.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">You do have to pay most of the money to the ma=
nagers.=C2=A0Burton also <a href=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com=
/click/32851551.261423/aHR0cHM6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9uZXdzL2FydGljbGVz=
LzIwMjMtMDktMjIvd2VpbnN0ZWluLXdvdWxkLW9mZmVyLXNjdWxwdG9yLWNsaWVudHMtc3dlZXR=
lbmVyLXRvLXN0YXktYXQtZmlybT9jbXBpZD1CQkQwOTI3MjNfTU9ORVlTVFVGRiZ1dG1fbWVkaX=
VtPWVtYWlsJnV0bV9zb3VyY2U9bmV3c2xldHRlciZ1dG1fdGVybT0yMzA5MjcmdXRtX2NhbXBha=
WduPW1vbmV5c3R1ZmY/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBb7c0038b" itemprop=3D"StoryLink=
" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: #000000; text-d=
ecoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border-bottom-color: =
#000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;"> reported las=
t week</a>:</p>
<blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">Boaz Weinstein would offer Sculptor Capital Ma=
nagement Inc. clients the chance to join his investment in the money manage=
r under the same terms as his billionaire backers, according to people fami=
liar with the plan.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">The Saba Capital Management founder and his co=
-investors view the plan as a sweetener for clients, who must give their ap=
proval in order for Weinstein=E2=80=99s bid for Sculptor to go through.</p>
</blockquote>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">It=E2=80=99s an odd sweetener? The reason that=
 Sculptor=E2=80=99s board has given for preferring Rithm is that Rithm woul=
d keep Levin, and it thinks that Sculptor=E2=80=99s clients would prefer to=
 have Levin manage their money rather than Weinstein. (Since, after all, th=
ey <em>are=C2=A0</em>still clients of Sculptor, which Levin runs, and they =
are not currently=C2=A0clients of Saba, which Weinstein runs.) We have <a h=
ref=3D"https://link.mail.bloombergbusiness.com/click/32851551.261423/aHR0cH=
M6Ly93d3cuYmxvb21iZXJnLmNvbS9vcGluaW9uL2FydGljbGVzLzIwMjMtMDktMTgvc2N1bHB0b=
3Itc3RpY2tzLXdpdGgtdGhlLWRlYWwtaXQta25vd3M_Y21waWQ9QkJEMDkyNzIzX01PTkVZU1RV=
RkYmdXRtX21lZGl1bT1lbWFpbCZ1dG1fc291cmNlPW5ld3NsZXR0ZXImdXRtX3Rlcm09MjMwOTI=
3JnV0bV9jYW1wYWlnbj1tb25leXN0dWZm/607f07ceef4b8524a319a23cBe0a067d8" itempr=
op=3D"StoryLink" itemscope=3D"itemscope" target=3D"_blank" style=3D"color: =
#000000; text-decoration: none !important; border-bottom-width: 1px; border=
-bottom-color: #000000; border-bottom-style: solid; background-color: #ccc;=
"> talked about this situation a lot</a>; Sculptor=E2=80=99s reasoning stri=
kes me as plausible but weirdly uncertain. (Why not ask the clients?) By of=
fering the clients a sweetener, Weinstein is trying to reassure the board t=
hat the clients will consent to him taking over.</p>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">But why would the clients want to own the firm=
? I feel like the lesson of Sculptor is:</p>
<ol style=3D"list-style-type: decimal; padding-left: 40px; margin: 16px 0;"=
>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">A well-run hedge fund probably makes =
money for its <em>clients</em>. (Though Sculptor=E2=80=99s =E2=80=9Cmain fu=
nd has annualized at about 6% since 2018, and its returns more closely trac=
k the S&amp;P 500 than other multi-strategy firms,=E2=80=9D report Burton a=
nd Parmar.)</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;">It definitely makes mo=
ney for its=C2=A0<em>managers</em>.</li>=09<li style=3D"margin-bottom: 5px;=
">The=C2=A0<em>shareholders of the management company</em>, not necessarily=
?</li>
</ol>
<p style=3D"margin: 16px 0;">You have to make money for the clients, you ha=
ve to pay the investment managers, and the shareholders just get what=E2=80=
=99s left over. It makes total sense for Weinstein to want to=C2=A0<em>buy =
and run=C2=A0</em>Sculptor; it makes a bit less sense for anyone else to wa=
nt to=C2=A0<em>help him buy it=C2=A0</em>as an outside=C2=A0passive investo=
r. Though I guess Ackman, Lasry and Yass are in, which is an endorsement of=
 the idea. Presumably they have to get paid too.</p>
